    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="topic-heading">UPSC Civil Services Examination Notes</h2>

        <div class="section">
            <h3>History</h3>
            <ul class="notes-list">
                <li><strong>Ancient History:</strong> Indus Valley Civilization, Vedic Age, Mauryan and Gupta Empires.</li>
                <li><strong>Medieval History:</strong> Delhi Sultanate, Mughal Empire, Bhakti & Sufi Movements.</li>
                <li><strong>Modern History:</strong> Revolt of 1857, Indian National Movement, Post-Independence India.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Important Date:</strong> 1857 – First War of Independence.</p>
            <p><strong>Case Study:</strong> Role of Gandhi in Non-Cooperation Movement (1920-22).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h3>Polity & Governance</h3>
            <ul class="notes-list">
                <li><strong>Indian Constitution:</strong> Preamble, Fundamental Rights & Duties, Directive Principles.</li>
                <li><strong>Parliament & Judiciary:</strong> Lok Sabha, Rajya Sabha, Supreme Court, High Courts.</li>
                <li><strong>Governance & Policies:</strong> Panchayati Raj, Centre-State Relations, Public Administration.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Important Article:</strong> Article 32 - Right to Constitutional Remedies.</p>
            <p><strong>Case Study:</strong> Keshavananda Bharati Case (1973) – Basic Structure Doctrine.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h3>Indian Economy</h3>
            <ul class="notes-list">
                <li><strong>Basic Concepts:</strong> GDP, Inflation, Fiscal Deficit, Monetary Policy.</li>
                <li><strong>Five-Year Plans:</strong> Objectives and Achievements from 1951 to Present.</li>
                <li><strong>Economic Reforms:</strong> 1991 LPG (Liberalization, Privatization, Globalization) Reforms.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Key Formula:</strong> GDP = C + I + G + (X - M)</p>
            <p><strong>Case Study:</strong> Demonetization (2016) – Impact on Economy and Digital Transactions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h3>Geography</h3>
            <ul class="notes-list">
                <li><strong>Physical Geography:</strong> Landforms, Climate, Ocean Currents, Natural Disasters.</li>
                <li><strong>Human Geography:</strong> Population, Migration, Urbanization.</li>
                <li><strong>Indian Geography:</strong> Himalayas, Monsoon System, River Systems.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Key Concept:</strong> El Niño Effect on Indian Monsoon.</p>
            <p><strong>Case Study:</strong> Chennai Floods (2015) – Role of Urban Planning in Disaster Management.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h3>Science & Technology</h3>
            <ul class="notes-list">
                <li><strong>Space Technology:</strong> ISRO Missions – Chandrayaan, Mangalyaan, Gaganyaan.</li>
                <li><strong>Biotechnology:</strong> DNA Sequencing, CRISPR, Vaccination Programs.</li>
                <li><strong>Artificial Intelligence:</strong> AI in Healthcare, Robotics, Machine Learning.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Recent Development:</strong> India’s AI Mission & Role of Startups.</p>
            <p><strong>Case Study:</strong> COVID-19 Vaccine Development in India (Covaxin & Covishield).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h3>Environment & Ecology</h3>
            <ul class="notes-list">
                <li><strong>Environmental Issues:</strong> Climate Change, Air & Water Pollution, Deforestation.</li>
                <li><strong>Conservation Efforts:</strong> National Parks, Wildlife Protection, Eco-sensitive Zones.</li>
                <li><strong>International Agreements:</strong> Paris Climate Agreement, Kyoto Protocol, COP26.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Important Date:</strong> Earth Summit – 1992.</p>
            <p><strong>Case Study:</strong> Chipko Movement – Role of Communities in Forest Conservation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h3>Current Affairs</h3>
            <p>Stay updated with daily news related to politics, economy, international relations, and major government policies.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> India's G20 Presidency (2023) – Key Outcomes.</p>
        </div>

